This is a song sung by Edith Piaf after she lost the lover of her life, Marcel Cerdan, a boxing champion, in an airplane accident. Edith Piaf sang about overcoming the pain of losing Marcel, but Celine Dion sang about her own perseverance and the loss of her loved one - that if the world takes you away and breaks me down, I will overcome it and still cherish my love for you. The song was particularly meaningful and poetic as it came after her illness, as a promise to her fans that she would return to the stage again. She sang not just for herself but as a tribute to the athletes who participated in the Olympic Games - to put an end to the long journey of overcoming difficult battles with themselves and to finally bear fruit...and finally as a tribute to humanity that continues to overcome hardships and keep going. It is an ode to our love towards humanity and that no matter how difficult the suffering, together, we will persevere. Thank you Celine Dion.
